JOHANNESBURG - Eskom and trade unions have signed a new wage agreement on Tuesday afternoon. This guarantees workers a 7% wage increase across the board and R400 hikes in housing allowance. The deal follows weeks of tensions, that saw a strike at the utility's plants and the return of stage 6 load shedding. BREAKING NEWS: Its a done deal! #Eskom and trade unions are signing a new wage agreement guaranteeing workers 7% wage increases. This follows weeks of tensions, which came to a head through a wildcat/unlawful strike. TTM #NUM #Numsa #Solidarity pic.twitter.com/LriExsGAUO 